-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Wed Dec 10, 2014 06:17AM EST
-- None



Dec 10 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1100 GMT on Wednesday:

** British gas giant BG Group Plc <BG.L> said would sell its Australian QCLNG Pipeline business for $5 billion to APA Group <APA.AX>. [ID:nL1N0TT2F6]  ** Chinese conglomerate Fosun International Ltd <0656.HK>, controlled by billionaire Guo Guangchang, is set to raise its offer for French holiday group Club Mediterranee SA <CMIP.PA> to outbid Italian tycoon Andrea Bonomi, The Financial Times reported. [ID:nL6N0TU1AB]  ** Belden Inc <BDC.N>, a maker of networking and cable products, said it would buy Tripwire, a Portland-based cybersecurity firm, for $710 million. [ID:nL3N0TU1JR]  ** The chairman and chief executive of Tencent Holdings Ltd <0700.HK> has cashed in shares worth HK$3 billion ($387 million)in the Chinese internet firm this month, according to regulatory filings made with the Hong Kong Stock Exchange. [ID:nL1N0TU04K]  ** Australia's Fortescue Metals Group Ltd <FMG.AX> is willing to sell down stakes in some of its assets amid a collapse in iron ore prices, but the world's fourth-biggest iron ore miner says it is under no pressure to take quick action. [ID:nL3N0TT2H3]  ** Banca Transilvania SA <ROTLV.BX>, Romania's third-biggest bank, will buy part-nationalized Austrian lender Volksbanken AG's <OTVVp.VI> Romanian business in a deal triggered by Volksbanken's radical shrinking cure, the Austrian bank said. [ID:nL6N0TU12A]  ** An Orascom subsidiary has approved the sale of 140 million Egyptian pounds ($19.6 million) of assets to Accelero Capital group, Orascom said. [ID:nL6N0TU12J]  ** Czech beer group Pivovary Lobkowicz Group <PLG.PR> has taken full control of its Rychtar brewery after exercising an option to buy the 30 percent share it did not own, the company said. [ID:nL6N0TU1KA]